gral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∫</a> (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F'</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">x₀</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Differentiation under integral of `x ↦ ∫ F x a` at a given point `x₀`, assuming `F x₀` is\nintegrable, `‖F x a - F x₀ a‖ ≤ bound a * ‖x - x₀‖` for `x` in a neighborhood of `x₀` for ae `a`\nintegrable Lipschitz bound `bound` (with a neighborhood independent of `a`), and `F x` is\nae-measurable for `x` in the same ball. See `hasFDerivAt_integral_of_dominated_loc_of_lip` for a\nslightly less general but usually more useful version. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ParametricIntegral.html#hasFDerivAt_integral_of_dominated_loc_of_lip'","kind":"theorem","line":73,"name":"hasFDerivAt_integral_of_dominated_loc_of_lip'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/ParametricIntegral.lean#L73-L160"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.MeanValue","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.DominatedConvergence","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Integral.Bochner.Set","Mathlib.Analysis.LocallyConvex.SeparatingDual"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.ParametricIntegral"}